    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="522"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d522">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.91/12–844</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by President <persName type="from"
                            >Roosevelt</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Warm Springs, Georgia</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-08">December 8,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I think this Soviet-Iranian matter should be taken up by Harriman with Stalin in
                    person. The Teheran agreement was pretty definite and my contribution was to
                    suggest to Stalin and Churchill that three or four Trustees build a new port in
                    Iran at the head of the Persian Gulf (free port), take over the whole railroad
                    from there into Russia, and run the thing for the good of all. Stalin’s comment
                    was merely that it was an interesting idea and he offered no objection.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >oosevelt</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
